items.name: Mutable-and-Immutable-Borrows-Conflict-in-Rust-w2at7
items.description: Demonstrates a common error in Rust related to mutable and immutable borrows of the same variable.  This example shows why attempting to use an immutable reference (&) after creating a mutable reference (&mut) to the same variable leads to a compile-time error.
